ce Theatre Stamford.jpg|[[Stamford Center for the Arts|The Palace Theatre]] at Stamford Center for the Arts in Downtown Stamford\nFile:Stamford Government Center - 888 Washington Blvd.jpg|Stamford Government Center, the city's municipal offices\nFile:Alive@Five Stamford Boyz II Men.jpg|[[Boyz II Men]] performing at the 2015 Alive@Five Summer Concert Series hosted by [[Downtown Stamford|Stamford Downtown]]\nFile:Stamford CT Old Town Hall.jpg|Stamford's [[Old Town Hall (Stamford, Connecticut)|Old Town Hall]]\u2014a [[Beaux-Arts architecture|beaux arts]] building\nFile:Stamford Museum & Nature Center Bendel Mansion.jpg|The [[Henri Willis Bendel|Henri Bendel]] Mansion at the [[Stamford Museum & Nature Center]]\nFile:UCONN Stamford Building.jpg|[[University of Connecticut#Stamford campus|UCONN Stamford's]] main campus building\nFile:Ferguson Library Stamford.jpg|The Ferguson Library in [[Downtown Stamford]]\n</gallery>\n\n==Demographics==\n\n{{US Census population\n|1880= 2540\n|1890= 10396\n|1900= 15997|1910= 25138\n|1920= 35096\n|1930= 46346\n|1940= 47938\n|1950= 74293\n|1960= 92713\n|1970= 108798\n|1980= 102466\n|1990= 108056\n|2000= 117083\n|2010= 122643\n|estyear=2018\n|estimate=129775\n|estref=<ref name=\"USCensusEst2018\">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov/programs-surveys/popest/data/tables.2018.html|title=Population and Housing Unit Estimates|accessdate=July 16, 2019}}</ref>\n|align-fn=center\n|footnote=[https://www.census.gov/programs-surveys/decennial-census.html U.S. Decennial Census]<br />2018 Estimate<ref name=\"2018 Pop Estimate\">{{cite web|title=Population Estimates|url=https://census.gov/data/tables/2018/demo/popest/total-cities-and-towns.html|publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]]|accessdate=June 8, 2018}}</ref>\n}}\n\nThe [[population density]] is 3,101.9 people per square mile (1,197.5/km<sup>2</sup>).\n\n===Age and gender===\nThe proportion of the population under the age of 18 was 21.6%, age 18 to 24 was 7.8%, age 25 to 44 was 32.5%, age 45 to 64 was 25.0%, and 65 years of age or older was 13.1%. The median age of 37.1 is slightly lower than the U.S. median age of 37.2. Composition of the population based on sex is 50.7 females to 49.3 males. (Source: 2000 U.S. Census)\n\n===Education===\nStamford has one of the most highly educated populations in the U.S.\u2014nine out of ten are high school graduates, and those possessing a bachelor's degree or higher is estimated at 43.6% of the population. Stamford is tied with [[Iowa City, Iowa]] for the U.S. metropolitan area with the highest percentage of the adult population holding a [[bachelor's degree]] or higher; 44 percent of adults hold a degree.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov|title=Census.gov|author=US Census Bureau|website=Census.gov}}</ref>\n\n===Ethnicity and race===\n2017 Census Statistics counted Stamford's population to be 131,000. A 2009 Census survey estimated 48,676 housing units to be in existence. Stamford's population characteristics are as follows (Source: Statistical Atlas, 2019)\n* [[White American|White]] 49.6%\n* [[Hispanic]] 25.4%\n* [[African American|Black]] 15.0%\n* [[Asian American|Asian]] 8.2%\n* Two or More Races 1.4%\n* All Other Races 0.4%\n\nMore than one out of three residents (35%) is foreign born. A language other than English is spoken at home by 45% of the population. The main ancestries of the population (Source: 2013 American Community Survey Estimate) are: Italian (12.4%), Irish (5.9%), Polish (4.5%), English (2.9%), German (2.9%), and Russian (2.3%). The top ten countries of origin for the foreign-born population (Source: 2010 US Census Bureau) are:\n[[File:StamfordHarbor.jpg|alt=|thumb|350px|Stamford Harbor. Stamford Harbor Park (office buildings) is in the background.]]\n\n* Dominican Republic 8,144\n* Guatemala 7,707\n* India 5,133\n* Haiti 5,071\n* Jamaica 2,753\n* Colombia 2,679\n* Peru 2,560\n* Mexico 2,478\n* Ecuador 2,313\n* China 1,991\n* Honduras 1,279\n\n===Housing===\nThere are 47,317 housing units at an average density of 1,253.6 per square mile (484.0/km<sup>2</sup>). There are 45,399 households out of which 28.7% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 48.5% were married couples living together, 11.5% had a female householder with no husband present, and 36.2% were non-families. 28.7% of all households were made up of individuals and 9.8% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 2.54 and the average family size was 3.13.\n\n===Income===\n{{See also|List of Connecticut locations by per capita income}}\n\nAccording to a 2007 estimate, the median income for a household in the city was $72,315, and the median income for a family was $88,205.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://factfinder.census.gov/servlet/ACSSAFFFacts?_event=ChangeGeoContext&geo_id=16000US0973000&_geoContext=01000US%7C04000US09%7C16000US0955990&_street=&_county=stamford&_cityTown=stamford&_state=04000US09&_zip=&_lang=en&_sse=on&ActiveGeoDiv=geoSelect&_useEV=&pctxt=fph&pgsl=010&_submenuId=factsheet_1&ds_name=ACS_2006_SAFF&_ci_nbr=null&qr_name=null&reg=null:null&_keyword=&_industry=|title=American FactFinder\u2014Community Facts|first=U.S. Census|last=Bureau|website=Factfinder.census.gov|access-date=March 26, 2018|archive-url=https://archive.today/20200211180313/http://factfinder.census.gov/servlet/ACSSAFFFacts?_event=ChangeGeoContext&geo_id=16000US0973000&_geoContext=01000US%7C04000US09%7C16000US0955990&_street=&_county=stamford&_cityTown=stamford&_state=04000US09&_zip=&_lang=en&_sse=on&ActiveGeoDiv=geoSelect&_useEV=&pctxt=fph&pgsl=010&_submenuId=factsheet_1&ds_name=ACS_2006_SAFF&_ci_nbr=null&qr_name=null&reg=null:null&_keyword=&_industry=|archive-date=February 11, 2020|url-status=dead}}</ref> Males had a median income of $48,386 versus $36,958 for females. The [[per capita income]] for the city was $34,987. About 5.4% of families and 7.9% of the population were below the [[Poverty threshold|poverty line]], including 8.7% of those under age 18 and 9.7% of those age 65 or over.\n\n==Politics==\n{| class=wikitable\n! colspan = 7 | Voter registration and party enrollment as of November 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://portal.ct.gov/-/media/sots/ElectionServices/Registration_and_Enrollment_Stats/Nov17RPES.pdf?la=en|format=PDF|title=Connecticut Secretary of the State: Registration and Party Enrollment Statistics as of November 1, 2017, based on reports as provided to the Secretary of the State by the Registrars of Voters|website=Portal.ct.gov|accessdate=21 January 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n! colspan = 2 | Party\n! Active voters\n! Inactive voters\n! Total voters\n! Percent Change Since 2014<ref>{{cite web|title=Registration and Party Enrollment Statistics as of October 30, 2014 |publisher=Connecticut Secretary of State |accessdate=April 26, 2015 |url=http://www.sots.ct.gov/sots/lib/sots/electionservices/registration_and_enrollment_stats/nov14re_(2).pdf |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060923151511/http://www.sots.ct.gov/sots/lib/sots/electionservices/registration_and_enrollment_stats/nov14re_%282%29.pdf |archivedate=September 23, 2006 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n! Percentage\n|-\n{{party color|Republican Party (United States)}}\n| [[Connecticut Republican Party|Republican]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 13,742\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 524\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 14,266\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| +7.7%\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 20.1%\n|-\n{{party color|Democratic Party (United States)}}\n| [[Democratic Party of Connecticut|Democratic]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 27,471\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 1,145\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 28,616\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| +13.9%\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 40.2%\n|-\n{{party color|Independent Party (United States)}}\n| [[Unaffiliated voter|Unaffiliated]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 25,377\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 1,420\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 26,797\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| +16%\n|